<br>
It is not really possible to install two version of EQ as when you try to install EQ the second time, EQ detects that a version of EQ has already been installed. However, you can just copy the first installation of EQ to another directory and it works fine.<br>
<br>
This method really bogs down your computer, especially during zonning. I do not recommend zonning both characters at the same time. Also turning off sound in one or both EQ installations helps tremendously. Turn off sound by placing an empty text file called &quot;nosound.txt&quot; in your EQ directory.<br>
<br>
Often, when you switch between windows while using the above method, your mouse cursor of one window seems to freeze. To unfreeze it, do a &quot;ctrl-alt-R&quot; to get your Windows cursor, and then click back onto the EQ Window to get back your EQ cursor. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kraye>Kraye</A> at: 8/28/03 11:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=enheduannalia>EnheduannaLia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The girl is about to do something stupid.</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/28/03 11:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4817.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.redhills.com/img/annapix.jpg height=150 width=78></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My own two account one Comp question.</span><hr size=1> There are a lot of good suggestions in this thread. I just thought I'd describe my set-up since I seem to be doing just fine with a much less powerful system than others.<br>
<br>
I play on a laptop. 800MHz, 512 MB, ATI graphics chip that was not the hottest even when it was new, 3 years ago. I almost always have two characters active. I mean, working together, not sitting in the bazaar. And I'm doing it with a modem connection that is usually 40K-48K. (If I can't get a 40K connection I only use one character.)<br>
<br>
In order to make that work I had to make a few compromises, hehe. Both chars *must* run at the same screen resolution, and that resolution *must* be the same as the windows screen resolution. Anything else and it becomes so slow it is unuseable. I use 800x600. I turned off all Luclin models except for the one character plus horse needed to use the horse. I keep the clip plane fairly low, and use 16bit graphics, because it works best with my hardware.<br>
<br>
I usually zone both characters at the SAME time because it works better for me. They both finish zoning faster, most of the time.<br>
<br>
As someone suggested, I too need to do a simultaneous login. Get one to server select, get the other there, get the first to char select, then the other, then finish boh. If I do any other sequence I get the &quot;Can't initialize EQMAIN.DLL&quot; error someone mentioned. If one crashes, I have to log the other out and start over with both. Fortunately, I haven't been having too many crashes lately, hehe.<br>
<br>
This works best for me using EQW. It also works with just plain EQ but I prefer the keyboard options of EQW. Besides, at the end of the day I can just use the Windows menu to close the EQW window, but EQ doesn't allow that.<br>
<br>
I used to only have one Everquest directory. After a few hotkeys got mixed up between them (causing an hour-long CR) I made a copy of the Everquest directory for each character. (Plus a third for beta now.) That eats a lot of disk space...<br>
<br>
The lesson here is that you can probably run two chars on any machine, but you may have to fiddle around a while to get acceptable performance.<br>
<br>
BTW: does anyone have an idea why I might have problems initializing EQMAIN.DLL when I have two full directories of software? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=237657"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.redhills.com/img/enannsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=haivane>Haivane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/28/03 12:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4817.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My own two account one Comp question.</span><hr size=1> *shakes her head confusingly*<br>
